    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <para>To remove the input shaft and bearing cap, remove the four retaining bolts (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302354">Figure 54</hotlnk>). Pull the shaft from the housing. It may be helpful to place
            two bolts in the threaded bearing cap holes. Tightening the bolts will draw the bearing cap from the
            housing. Tap the input shaft out of the bearing cap.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302354" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302354" filename="../figg13/G1302354.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 54. Input Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
